{116100}{Gnomish Entrepreneur

Stella was never meant to appear on any passenger manifest. A gnomish woman with a sharp eye for trade and survival, she learned early that people often mistake small size for small ambition. Stella has used that mistake to her advantage in counting houses, market stalls, and more than one back-room negotiation.

Now bound for Tarant aboard the IFS Zephyr, Stella is chasing more than money. She wants proof that opportunity belongs to the clever, not merely the tall, the titled, or the loud. If the new age belongs to those willing to seize it, she intends to arrive first and leave with interest.}
{116101}{Halfling Wanderer

Loretta grew up hearing that halfling women were meant for hearth, home, and quiet work done out of sight. She listened politely, smiled when expected, and spent her free hours learning how far a soft step and a stubborn heart could carry her. By the time anyone noticed she wanted a wider world, she had already saved enough coin for passage.

The IFS Zephyr is meant to take her to Tarant, but Loretta is looking for more than a city. She wants a life large enough to fit the person she has always known herself to be. Quiet, watchful, and harder to frighten than she looks, Loretta is ready to find out what Arcanum has been keeping from her.}
{1091}{Dwarven Outcast

Dagna Stonebrow learned early that a clan can forgive almost anything except refusing the part they wrote for you. She kept the hammer, kept the grit, and walked away from the rest.

Now she rides toward Tarant with the stubbornness of a dwarf and a story nobody else gets to name for her. She knows the city will not make room for her unless she takes it the hard way, and she has never expected kindness to do the work of courage. If Arcanum intends to test her, Dagna means to answer with steady hands, a harder will, and no apology for surviving on her own terms.}
